8 /// \file ----
9 /// Finalize v8.1-m low-overhead loops by converting the associated pseudo ----
10 /// instructions into machine operations. ----
11 /// The expectation is that the loop contains three pseudo instructions: ----
12 /// - t2*LoopStart - placed in the preheader or pre-preheader. The do-loop ----
13 /// form should be in the preheader, whereas the while form should be in the ----
14 /// preheaders only predecessor. ----
15 /// - t2LoopDec - placed within in the loop body. ----
16 /// - t2LoopEnd - the loop latch terminator. ----
17 /// ----
18 /// In addition to this, we also look for the presence of the VCTP instruction, ----
19 /// which determines whether we can generated the tail-predicated low-overhead ----
20 /// loop form. ----
21 /// ----
22 /// Assumptions and Dependencies: ----
23 /// Low-overhead loops are constructed and executed using a setup instruction: ----
24 /// DLS, WLS, DLSTP or WLSTP and an instruction that loops back: LE or LETP. ----
25 /// WLS(TP) and LE(TP) are branching instructions with a (large) limited range ----
26 /// but fixed polarity: WLS can only branch forwards and LE can only branch ----
27 /// backwards. These restrictions mean that this pass is dependent upon block ----
28 /// layout and block sizes, which is why it's the last pass to run. The same is ----
29 /// true for ConstantIslands, but this pass does not increase the size of the ----
30 /// basic blocks, nor does it change the CFG. Instructions are mainly removed ----
31 /// during the transform and pseudo instructions are replaced by real ones. In ----
32 /// some cases, when we have to revert to a 'normal' loop, we have to introduce ----
33 /// multiple instructions for a single pseudo (see RevertWhile and ----
34 /// RevertLoopEnd). To handle this situation, t2WhileLoopStartLR and t2LoopEnd ----
35 /// are defined to be as large as this maximum sequence of replacement ----
36 /// instructions. ----
37 /// ----
38 /// A note on VPR.P0 (the lane mask): ----
39 /// VPT, VCMP, VPNOT and VCTP won't overwrite VPR.P0 when they update it in a ----
40 /// "VPT Active" context (which includes low-overhead loops and vpt blocks). ----
41 /// They will simply "and" the result of their calculation with the current ----
42 /// value of VPR.P0. You can think of it like this: ----
43 /// \verbatim ----
44 /// if VPT active: ; Between a DLSTP/LETP, or for predicated instrs ----
45 /// VPR.P0 &= Value ----
46 /// else ----
47 /// VPR.P0 = Value ----
48 /// \endverbatim ----
49 /// When we're inside the low-overhead loop (between DLSTP and LETP), we always ----
50 /// fall in the "VPT active" case, so we can consider that all VPR writes by ----
51 /// one of those instruction is actually a "and". ----
52 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----

89 static bool isVectorPredicated(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
90 int PIdx = llvm::findFirstVPTPredOperandIdx(*MI); 0
91 return PIdx != -1 && MI->getOperand(PIdx + 1).getReg() == ARM::VPR; 0
92 } ----

96 } ----

100 } ----

103 uint64_t Domain = MI->getDesc().TSFlags & ARMII::DomainMask; 0
104 return Domain == ARMII::DomainMVE; 0

108 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MI.getDesc(); 0
109 uint64_t Flags = MCID.TSFlags; 0

111 } ----

137 // Visit all the blocks within the loop, as well as exit blocks and any ----
138 // blocks properly dominating the header. ----
139 void ProcessLoop() { 0
140 std::function Search = [this, &Search] 0
141 (MachineBasicBlock *MBB) -> void { 0
142 if (Visited.count(MBB)) 0
143 return; 0
144 ----
145 Visited.insert(MBB); 0
146 for (auto *Succ : MBB->successors()) { 0
147 if (!ML.contains(Succ)) 0
148 continue; 0
149 Search(Succ); 0
150 } ----
151 Order.push_back(MBB); 0
152 }; 0
153 ----
154 // Insert exit blocks. ----
155 SmallVector ExitBlocks; 0
156 ML.getExitBlocks(ExitBlocks); 0
157 append_range(Order, ExitBlocks); 0
158 ----
159 // Then add the loop body. ----
160 Search(ML.getHeader()); 0
161 ----
162 // Then try the preheader and its predecessors. ----
163 std::function GetPredecessor = ----
164 [this, &GetPredecessor] (MachineBasicBlock *MBB) -> void { 0
165 Order.push_back(MBB); 0
166 if (MBB->pred_size() == 1) 0
167 GetPredecessor(*MBB->pred_begin()); 0
168 }; 0
169 ----
170 if (auto *Preheader = ML.getLoopPreheader()) 0
171 GetPredecessor(Preheader); 0
172 else if (auto *Preheader = MLI.findLoopPreheader(&ML, true, true)) 0
173 GetPredecessor(Preheader); 0
174 } 0
175 }; ----

188 // Represent the current state of the VPR and hold all instances which ----
189 // represent a VPT block, which is a list of instructions that begins with a ----
190 // VPT/VPST and has a maximum of four proceeding instructions. All ----
191 // instructions within the block are predicated upon the vpr and we allow ----
192 // instructions to define the vpr within in the block too. ----

203 static void CreateVPTBlock(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
204 assert((CurrentPredicates.size() || MI->getParent()->isLiveIn(ARM::VPR)) 0
205 && "Can't begin VPT without predicate"); ----
206 Blocks.emplace_back(MI); 0
207 // The execution of MI is predicated upon the current set of instructions ----
208 // that are AND'ed together to form the VPR predicate value. In the case ----
209 // that MI is a VPT, CurrentPredicates will also just be MI. ----
210 PredicatedInsts.emplace( 0
211 MI, std::make_unique(MI, CurrentPredicates)); 0
212 } 0
213 ----
214 static void reset() { 0
215 Blocks.clear(); 0
216 PredicatedInsts.clear(); 0
217 CurrentPredicates.clear(); 0
218 } 0
219 ----
220 static void addInst(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
221 Blocks.back().insert(MI); 0
222 PredicatedInsts.emplace( 0
223 MI, std::make_unique(MI, CurrentPredicates)); 0
224 } 0

257 static bool isPredicatedOnVCTP(MachineInstr *MI, bool Exclusive = false) { 0
258 SetVector &Predicates = PredicatedInsts[MI]->Predicates; 0
259 if (Exclusive && Predicates.size() != 1) 0

271 // If this block begins with a VPT, we can check whether it's using ----
272 // at least one predicated input(s), as well as possible loop invariant ----
273 // which would result in it being implicitly predicated. ----
274 static bool hasImplicitlyValidVPT(VPTState &Block, 0
275 ReachingDefAnalysis &RDA) { ----
276 SmallVectorImpl &Insts = Block.getInsts(); 0
277 MachineInstr *VPT = Insts.front(); 0
278 assert(isVPTOpcode(VPT->getOpcode()) && 0
279 "Expected VPT block to begin with VPT/VPST"); ----
280 ----
281 if (VPT->getOpcode() == ARM::MVE_VPST) 0

283 ----
284 auto IsOperandPredicated = [&](MachineInstr *MI, unsigned Idx) { 0
285 MachineInstr *Op = RDA.getMIOperand(MI, MI->getOperand(Idx)); 0
286 return Op && PredicatedInsts.count(Op) && isPredicatedOnVCTP(Op); 0
287 }; 0
288 ----
289 auto IsOperandInvariant = [&](MachineInstr *MI, unsigned Idx) { 0
290 MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(Idx); 0
291 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.getReg()) 0
292 return true; 0
293 ----
294 SmallPtrSet Defs; 0
295 RDA.getGlobalReachingDefs(MI, MO.getReg(), Defs); 0
296 if (Defs.empty()) 0
297 return true; 0
298 ----
299 for (auto *Def : Defs) 0
300 if (Def->getParent() == VPT->getParent()) 0
301 return false; 0
302 return true; 0
303 }; 0
304 ----
305 // Check that at least one of the operands is directly predicated on a ----
306 // vctp and allow an invariant value too. ----
307 return (IsOperandPredicated(VPT, 1) || IsOperandPredicated(VPT, 2)) && 0
308 (IsOperandPredicated(VPT, 1) || IsOperandInvariant(VPT, 1)) && 0
309 (IsOperandPredicated(VPT, 2) || IsOperandInvariant(VPT, 2)); 0
310 } ----
311 ----
312 static bool isValid(ReachingDefAnalysis &RDA) { 0
313 // All predication within the loop should be based on vctp. If the block ----
314 // isn't predicated on entry, check whether the vctp is within the block ----
315 // and that all other instructions are then predicated on it. ----
316 for (auto &Block : Blocks) { 0
317 if (isEntryPredicatedOnVCTP(Block, false) || 0
318 hasImplicitlyValidVPT(Block, RDA)) 0
319 continue; 0
320 ----
321 SmallVectorImpl &Insts = Block.getInsts(); 0
322 // We don't know how to convert a block with just a VPT;VCTP into ----
323 // anything valid once we remove the VCTP. For now just bail out. ----
324 assert(isVPTOpcode(Insts.front()->getOpcode()) && 0
325 "Expected VPT block to start with a VPST or VPT!"); ----
326 if (Insts.size() == 2 && Insts.front()->getOpcode() != ARM::MVE_VPST && 0
327 isVCTP(Insts.back())) 0
328 return false; 0
329 ----
330 for (auto *MI : Insts) { 0
331 // Check that any internal VCTPs are 'Then' predicated. ----
332 if (isVCTP(MI) && getVPTInstrPredicate(*MI) != ARMVCC::Then) 0
333 return false; 0
334 // Skip other instructions that build up the predicate. ----
335 if (MI->getOpcode() == ARM::MVE_VPST || isVectorPredicate(MI)) 0
336 continue; 0
337 // Check that any other instructions are predicated upon a vctp. ----
338 // TODO: We could infer when VPTs are implicitly predicated on the ----
339 // vctp (when the operands are predicated). ----
340 if (!isPredicatedOnVCTP(MI)) { 0
341 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Can't convert: " << *MI); 0
342 return false; 0
343 } ----
344 } ----
345 } ----
346 return true; 0
347 } ----

540 ----
541 static bool TryRemove(MachineInstr *MI, ReachingDefAnalysis &RDA, 0
542 InstSet &ToRemove, InstSet &Ignore) { ----
543 ----
544 // Check that we can remove all of Killed without having to modify any IT ----
545 // blocks. ----
546 auto WontCorruptITs = [](InstSet &Killed, ReachingDefAnalysis &RDA) { 0
547 // Collect the dead code and the MBBs in which they reside. ----
548 SmallPtrSet BasicBlocks; 0
549 for (auto *Dead : Killed) 0
550 BasicBlocks.insert(Dead->getParent()); 0
551 ----
552 // Collect IT blocks in all affected basic blocks. ----
553 std::map> ITBlocks; 0
554 for (auto *MBB : BasicBlocks) { 0
555 for (auto &IT : *MBB) { 0
556 if (IT.getOpcode() != ARM::t2IT) 0
557 continue; 0
558 RDA.getReachingLocalUses(&IT, MCRegister::from(ARM::ITSTATE), 0
559 ITBlocks[&IT]); 0
560 } ----
561 } ----
562 ----
563 // If we're removing all of the instructions within an IT block, then ----
564 // also remove the IT instruction. ----
565 SmallPtrSet ModifiedITs; 0
566 SmallPtrSet RemoveITs; 0
567 for (auto *Dead : Killed) { 0
568 if (MachineOperand *MO = Dead->findRegisterUseOperand(ARM::ITSTATE)) { 0
569 MachineInstr *IT = RDA.getMIOperand(Dead, *MO); 0
570 RemoveITs.insert(IT); 0
571 auto &CurrentBlock = ITBlocks[IT]; 0
572 CurrentBlock.erase(Dead); 0
573 if (CurrentBlock.empty()) 0
574 ModifiedITs.erase(IT); 0
575 else ----
576 ModifiedITs.insert(IT); 0
577 } ----
578 } ----
579 if (!ModifiedITs.empty()) 0
580 return false; 0
581 Killed.insert(RemoveITs.begin(), RemoveITs.end()); 0
582 return true; 0
583 }; 0
584 ----
585 SmallPtrSet Uses; 0
586 if (!RDA.isSafeToRemove(MI, Uses, Ignore)) 0
587 return false; 0
588 ----
589 if (WontCorruptITs(Uses, RDA)) { 0
590 ToRemove.insert(Uses.begin(), Uses.end()); 0
591 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Able to remove: " << *MI 0
592 << " - can also remove:\n"; ----
593 for (auto *Use : Uses) ----
594 dbgs() << " - " << *Use); ----
595 ----
596 SmallPtrSet Killed; 0
597 RDA.collectKilledOperands(MI, Killed); 0
598 if (WontCorruptITs(Killed, RDA)) { 0
599 ToRemove.insert(Killed.begin(), Killed.end()); 0
600 LLVM_DEBUG(for (auto *Dead : Killed) 0
601 dbgs() << " - " << *Dead); ----
602 } ----
603 return true; 0
604 } 0
605 return false; 0
606 } 0
607 ----
608 bool LowOverheadLoop::ValidateTailPredicate() { 0
609 if (!IsTailPredicationLegal()) { 0
610 LLVM_DEBUG(if (VCTPs.empty()) 0
611 dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Didn't find a VCTP instruction.\n"; ----
612 dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Tail-predication is not valid.\n"); ----
613 return false; 0
614 } ----
615 ----
616 assert(!VCTPs.empty() && "VCTP instruction expected but is not set"); 0
617 assert(ML.getBlocks().size() == 1 && 0
618 "Shouldn't be processing a loop with more than one block"); ----
619 ----
620 if (DisableTailPredication) { 0
621 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: tail-predication is disabled\n"); 0
622 return false; 0
623 } ----
624 ----
625 if (!VPTState::isValid(RDA)) { 0
626 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Invalid VPT state.\n"); 0
627 return false; 0
628 } ----
629 ----
630 if (!ValidateLiveOuts()) { 0
631 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Invalid live outs.\n"); 0
632 return false; 0
633 } ----
634 ----
635 // For tail predication, we need to provide the number of elements, instead ----
636 // of the iteration count, to the loop start instruction. The number of ----
637 // elements is provided to the vctp instruction, so we need to check that ----
638 // we can use this register at InsertPt. ----
639 MachineInstr *VCTP = VCTPs.back(); 0
640 if (Start->getOpcode() == ARM::t2DoLoopStartTP || 0
641 Start->getOpcode() == ARM::t2WhileLoopStartTP) { 0
642 TPNumElements = Start->getOperand(2); 0
643 StartInsertPt = Start; 0
644 StartInsertBB = Start->getParent(); 0
645 } else { ----
646 TPNumElements = VCTP->getOperand(1); 0
647 MCRegister NumElements = TPNumElements.getReg().asMCReg(); 0
648 ----
649 // If the register is defined within loop, then we can't perform TP. ----
650 // TODO: Check whether this is just a mov of a register that would be ----
651 // available. ----
652 if (RDA.hasLocalDefBefore(VCTP, NumElements)) { 0
653 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: VCTP operand is defined in the loop.\n"); 0
654 return false; 0
655 } ----
656 ----
657 // The element count register maybe defined after InsertPt, in which case we ----
658 // need to try to move either InsertPt or the def so that the [w|d]lstp can ----
659 // use the value. ----
660 ----
661 if (StartInsertPt != StartInsertBB->end() && 0
662 !RDA.isReachingDefLiveOut(&*StartInsertPt, NumElements)) { 0
663 if (auto *ElemDef = 0
664 RDA.getLocalLiveOutMIDef(StartInsertBB, NumElements)) { 0
665 if (RDA.isSafeToMoveForwards(ElemDef, &*StartInsertPt)) { 0
666 ElemDef->removeFromParent(); 0
667 StartInsertBB->insert(StartInsertPt, ElemDef); 0
668 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() 0
669 << "ARM Loops: Moved element count def: " << *ElemDef); ----
670 } else if (RDA.isSafeToMoveBackwards(&*StartInsertPt, ElemDef)) { 0
671 StartInsertPt->removeFromParent(); 0
672 StartInsertBB->insertAfter(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(ElemDef), 0
673 &*StartInsertPt); 0
674 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Moved start past: " << *ElemDef); 0
675 } else { ----
676 // If we fail to move an instruction and the element count is provided ----
677 // by a mov, use the mov operand if it will have the same value at the ----
678 // insertion point ----
679 MachineOperand Operand = ElemDef->getOperand(1); 0
680 if (isMovRegOpcode(ElemDef->getOpcode()) && 0
681 RDA.getUniqueReachingMIDef(ElemDef, Operand.getReg().asMCReg()) == 0
682 RDA.getUniqueReachingMIDef(&*StartInsertPt, 0
683 Operand.getReg().asMCReg())) { 0
684 TPNumElements = Operand; 0
685 NumElements = TPNumElements.getReg(); 0
686 } else { ----
687 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() 0
688 << "ARM Loops: Unable to move element count to loop " ----
689 << "start instruction.\n"); ----
690 return false; 0
691 } ----
692 } ----
693 } ----
694 } ----
695 ----
696 // Especially in the case of while loops, InsertBB may not be the ----
697 // preheader, so we need to check that the register isn't redefined ----
698 // before entering the loop. ----
699 auto CannotProvideElements = [this](MachineBasicBlock *MBB, 0
700 MCRegister NumElements) { 0
701 if (MBB->empty()) 0
702 return false; 0
703 // NumElements is redefined in this block. ----
704 if (RDA.hasLocalDefBefore(&MBB->back(), NumElements)) 0
705 return true; 0
706 ----
707 // Don't continue searching up through multiple predecessors. ----
708 if (MBB->pred_size() > 1) 0
709 return true; 0
710 ----
711 return false; 0
712 }; 0
713 ----
714 // Search backwards for a def, until we get to InsertBB. ----
715 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = Preheader; 0
716 while (MBB && MBB != StartInsertBB) { 0
717 if (CannotProvideElements(MBB, NumElements)) { 0
718 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Unable to provide element count.\n"); 0
719 return false; 0
720 } ----
721 MBB = *MBB->pred_begin(); 0
722 } ----
723 } ----
724 ----
725 // Could inserting the [W|D]LSTP cause some unintended affects? In a perfect ----
726 // world the [w|d]lstp instruction would be last instruction in the preheader ----
727 // and so it would only affect instructions within the loop body. But due to ----
728 // scheduling, and/or the logic in this pass (above), the insertion point can ----
729 // be moved earlier. So if the Loop Start isn't the last instruction in the ----
730 // preheader, and if the initial element count is smaller than the vector ----
731 // width, the Loop Start instruction will immediately generate one or more ----
732 // false lane mask which can, incorrectly, affect the proceeding MVE ----
733 // instructions in the preheader. ----
734 if (std::any_of(StartInsertPt, StartInsertBB->end(), shouldInspect)) { 0
735 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Instruction blocks [W|D]LSTP\n"); 0
736 return false; 0
737 } ----
738 ----
739 // For any DoubleWidthResultInstrs we found whilst scanning instructions, they ----
740 // need to compute an output size that is smaller than the VCTP mask operates ----
741 // on. The VecSize of the DoubleWidthResult is the larger vector size - the ----
742 // size it extends into, so any VCTP VecSize <= is valid. ----
743 unsigned VCTPVecSize = getVecSize(*VCTP); 0
744 for (MachineInstr *MI : DoubleWidthResultInstrs) { 0
745 unsigned InstrVecSize = getVecSize(*MI); 0
746 if (InstrVecSize > VCTPVecSize) { 0
747 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Double width result larger than VCTP " 0
748 << "VecSize:\n" << *MI); ----
749 return false; 0
750 } ----
751 } ----
752 ----
753 // Check that the value change of the element count is what we expect and ----
754 // that the predication will be equivalent. For this we need: ----
755 // NumElements = NumElements - VectorWidth. The sub will be a sub immediate ----
756 // and we can also allow register copies within the chain too. ----
757 auto IsValidSub = [](MachineInstr *MI, int ExpectedVecWidth) { 0
758 return -getAddSubImmediate(*MI) == ExpectedVecWidth; 0
759 }; ----
760 ----
761 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = VCTP->getParent(); 0
762 // Remove modifications to the element count since they have no purpose in a ----
763 // tail predicated loop. Explicitly refer to the vctp operand no matter which ----
764 // register NumElements has been assigned to, since that is what the ----
765 // modifications will be using ----
766 if (auto *Def = RDA.getUniqueReachingMIDef( 0
767 &MBB->back(), VCTP->getOperand(1).getReg().asMCReg())) { 0
768 SmallPtrSet ElementChain; 0
769 SmallPtrSet Ignore; 0
770 unsigned ExpectedVectorWidth = getTailPredVectorWidth(VCTP->getOpcode()); 0
771 ----
772 Ignore.insert(VCTPs.begin(), VCTPs.end()); 0
773 ----
774 if (TryRemove(Def, RDA, ElementChain, Ignore)) { 0
775 bool FoundSub = false; 0
776 ----
777 for (auto *MI : ElementChain) { 0
778 if (isMovRegOpcode(MI->getOpcode())) 0
779 continue; 0
780 ----
781 if (isSubImmOpcode(MI->getOpcode())) { 0
782 if (FoundSub || !IsValidSub(MI, ExpectedVectorWidth)) { 0
783 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Unexpected instruction in element" 0
784 " count: " << *MI); ----
785 return false; 0
786 } ----
787 FoundSub = true; 0
788 } else { ----
789 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Unexpected instruction in element" 0
790 " count: " << *MI); ----
791 return false; 0
792 } ----
793 } ----
794 ToRemove.insert(ElementChain.begin(), ElementChain.end()); 0
795 } ----
796 } 0
797 ----
798 // If we converted the LoopStart to a t2DoLoopStartTP/t2WhileLoopStartTP, we ----
799 // can also remove any extra instructions in the preheader, which often ----
800 // includes a now unused MOV. ----
801 if ((Start->getOpcode() == ARM::t2DoLoopStartTP || 0
802 Start->getOpcode() == ARM::t2WhileLoopStartTP) && 0
803 Preheader && !Preheader->empty() && 0
804 !RDA.hasLocalDefBefore(VCTP, VCTP->getOperand(1).getReg())) { 0
805 if (auto *Def = RDA.getUniqueReachingMIDef( 0
806 &Preheader->back(), VCTP->getOperand(1).getReg().asMCReg())) { 0
807 SmallPtrSet Ignore; 0
808 Ignore.insert(VCTPs.begin(), VCTPs.end()); 0
809 TryRemove(Def, RDA, ToRemove, Ignore); 0
810 } 0
811 } ----
812 ----
813 return true; 0
814 } ----
815 ----
816 static bool isRegInClass(const MachineOperand &MO, 0
817 const TargetRegisterClass *Class) { ----
818 return MO.isReg() && MO.getReg() && Class->contains(MO.getReg()); 0
819 } ----
820 ----
821 // MVE 'narrowing' operate on half a lane, reading from half and writing ----
822 // to half, which are referred to has the top and bottom half. The other ----
823 // half retains its previous value. ----
824 static bool retainsPreviousHalfElement(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
825 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MI.getDesc(); 0
826 uint64_t Flags = MCID.TSFlags; 0
827 return (Flags & ARMII::RetainsPreviousHalfElement) != 0; 0
828 } ----
829 ----
830 // Some MVE instructions read from the top/bottom halves of their operand(s) ----
831 // and generate a vector result with result elements that are double the ----
832 // width of the input. ----
833 static bool producesDoubleWidthResult(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
834 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MI.getDesc(); 0
835 uint64_t Flags = MCID.TSFlags; 0
836 return (Flags & ARMII::DoubleWidthResult) != 0; 0
837 } ----
838 ----
839 static bool isHorizontalReduction(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
840 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MI.getDesc(); 0
841 uint64_t Flags = MCID.TSFlags; 0
842 return (Flags & ARMII::HorizontalReduction) != 0; 0
843 } ----
844 ----
845 // Can this instruction generate a non-zero result when given only zeroed ----
846 // operands? This allows us to know that, given operands with false bytes ----
847 // zeroed by masked loads, that the result will also contain zeros in those ----
848 // bytes. ----
849 static bool canGenerateNonZeros(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
850 ----
851 // Check for instructions which can write into a larger element size, ----
852 // possibly writing into a previous zero'd lane. ----
853 if (producesDoubleWidthResult(MI)) 0
854 return true; 0
855 ----
856 switch (MI.getOpcode()) { 0
857 default: 0
858 break; 0
859 // FIXME: VNEG FP and -0? I think we'll need to handle this once we allow ----
860 // fp16 -> fp32 vector conversions. ----
861 // Instructions that perform a NOT will generate 1s from 0s. ----
862 case ARM::MVE_VMVN: 0
863 case ARM::MVE_VORN: ----
864 // Count leading zeros will do just that! ----
865 case ARM::MVE_VCLZs8: ----
866 case ARM::MVE_VCLZs16: ----
867 case ARM::MVE_VCLZs32: ----
868 return true; 0
869 } ----
870 return false; 0
871 } ----
872 ----
873 // Look at its register uses to see if it only can only receive zeros ----
874 // into its false lanes which would then produce zeros. Also check that ----
875 // the output register is also defined by an FalseLanesZero instruction ----
876 // so that if tail-predication happens, the lanes that aren't updated will ----
877 // still be zeros. ----
878 static bool producesFalseLanesZero(MachineInstr &MI, 0
879 const TargetRegisterClass *QPRs, ----
880 const ReachingDefAnalysis &RDA, ----
881 InstSet &FalseLanesZero) { ----
882 if (canGenerateNonZeros(MI)) 0
883 return false; 0
884 ----
885 bool isPredicated = isVectorPredicated(&MI); 0
886 // Predicated loads will write zeros to the falsely predicated bytes of the ----
887 // destination register. ----
888 if (MI.mayLoad()) 0
889 return isPredicated; 0
890 ----
891 auto IsZeroInit = [](MachineInstr *Def) { 0
892 return !isVectorPredicated(Def) && 0
893 Def->getOpcode() == ARM::MVE_VMOVimmi32 && 0
894 Def->getOperand(1).getImm() == 0; 0
895 }; ----
896 ----
897 bool AllowScalars = isHorizontalReduction(MI); 0
898 for (auto &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
899 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.getReg()) 0
900 continue; 0
901 if (!isRegInClass(MO, QPRs) && AllowScalars) 0
902 continue; 0
903 // Skip the lr predicate reg ----
904 int PIdx = llvm::findFirstVPTPredOperandIdx(MI); 0
905 if (PIdx != -1 && (int)MO.getOperandNo() == PIdx + 2) 0
906 continue; 0
907 ----
908 // Check that this instruction will produce zeros in its false lanes: ----
909 // - If it only consumes false lanes zero or constant 0 (vmov #0) ----
910 // - If it's predicated, it only matters that it's def register already has ----
911 // false lane zeros, so we can ignore the uses. ----
912 SmallPtrSet Defs; 0
913 RDA.getGlobalReachingDefs(&MI, MO.getReg(), Defs); 0
914 if (Defs.empty()) 0
915 return false; 0
916 for (auto *Def : Defs) { 0
917 if (Def == &MI || FalseLanesZero.count(Def) || IsZeroInit(Def)) 0
918 continue; 0
919 if (MO.isUse() && isPredicated) 0
920 continue; 0
921 return false; 0
922 } ----
923 } 0
924 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Always False Zeros: " << MI); 0
925 return true; 0
926 } ----
927 ----
928 bool LowOverheadLoop::ValidateLiveOuts() { 0
929 // We want to find out if the tail-predicated version of this loop will ----
930 // produce the same values as the loop in its original form. For this to ----
931 // be true, the newly inserted implicit predication must not change the ----
932 // the (observable) results. ----
933 // We're doing this because many instructions in the loop will not be ----
934 // predicated and so the conversion from VPT predication to tail-predication ----
935 // can result in different values being produced; due to the tail-predication ----
936 // preventing many instructions from updating their falsely predicated ----
937 // lanes. This analysis assumes that all the instructions perform lane-wise ----
938 // operations and don't perform any exchanges. ----
939 // A masked load, whether through VPT or tail predication, will write zeros ----
940 // to any of the falsely predicated bytes. So, from the loads, we know that ----
941 // the false lanes are zeroed and here we're trying to track that those false ----
942 // lanes remain zero, or where they change, the differences are masked away ----
943 // by their user(s). ----
944 // All MVE stores have to be predicated, so we know that any predicate load ----
945 // operands, or stored results are equivalent already. Other explicitly ----
946 // predicated instructions will perform the same operation in the original ----
947 // loop and the tail-predicated form too. Because of this, we can insert ----
948 // loads, stores and other predicated instructions into our Predicated ----
949 // set and build from there. ----
950 const TargetRegisterClass *QPRs = TRI.getRegClass(ARM::MQPRRegClassID); 0
951 SetVector FalseLanesUnknown; 0
952 SmallPtrSet FalseLanesZero; 0
953 SmallPtrSet Predicated; 0
954 MachineBasicBlock *Header = ML.getHeader(); 0
955 ----
956 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Validating Live outs\n"); 0
957 ----
958 for (auto &MI : *Header) { 0
959 if (!shouldInspect(MI)) 0
960 continue; 0
961 ----
962 if (isVCTP(&MI) || isVPTOpcode(MI.getOpcode())) 0
963 continue; 0
964 ----
965 bool isPredicated = isVectorPredicated(&MI); 0
966 bool retainsOrReduces = ----
967 retainsPreviousHalfElement(MI) || isHorizontalReduction(MI); 0
968 ----
969 if (isPredicated) 0
970 Predicated.insert(&MI); 0
971 if (producesFalseLanesZero(MI, QPRs, RDA, FalseLanesZero)) 0
972 FalseLanesZero.insert(&MI); 0
973 else if (MI.getNumDefs() == 0) 0
974 continue; 0
975 else if (!isPredicated && retainsOrReduces) { 0
976 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Unpredicated instruction that retainsOrReduces: " << MI); 0
977 return false; 0
978 } else if (!isPredicated && MI.getOpcode() != ARM::MQPRCopy) 0
979 FalseLanesUnknown.insert(&MI); 0
980 } ----
981 ----
982 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
983 dbgs() << " Predicated:\n"; ----
984 for (auto *I : Predicated) ----
985 dbgs() << " " << *I; ----
986 dbgs() << " FalseLanesZero:\n"; ----
987 for (auto *I : FalseLanesZero) ----
988 dbgs() << " " << *I; ----
989 dbgs() << " FalseLanesUnknown:\n"; ----
990 for (auto *I : FalseLanesUnknown) ----
991 dbgs() << " " << *I; ----
992 }); ----
993 ----
994 auto HasPredicatedUsers = [this](MachineInstr *MI, const MachineOperand &MO, 0
995 SmallPtrSetImpl &Predicated) { 0
996 SmallPtrSet Uses; 0
997 RDA.getGlobalUses(MI, MO.getReg().asMCReg(), Uses); 0
998 for (auto *Use : Uses) { 0
999 if (Use != MI && !Predicated.count(Use)) 0
1000 return false; 0
1001 } ----
1002 return true; 0
1003 }; 0
1004 ----
1005 // Visit the unknowns in reverse so that we can start at the values being ----
1006 // stored and then we can work towards the leaves, hopefully adding more ----
1007 // instructions to Predicated. Successfully terminating the loop means that ----
1008 // all the unknown values have to found to be masked by predicated user(s). ----
1009 // For any unpredicated values, we store them in NonPredicated so that we ----
1010 // can later check whether these form a reduction. ----
1011 SmallPtrSet NonPredicated; 0
1012 for (auto *MI : reverse(FalseLanesUnknown)) { 0
1013 for (auto &MO : MI->operands()) { 0
1014 if (!isRegInClass(MO, QPRs) || !MO.isDef()) 0
1015 continue; 0
1016 if (!HasPredicatedUsers(MI, MO, Predicated)) { 0
1017 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Found an unknown def of : " 0
1018 << TRI.getRegAsmName(MO.getReg()) << " at " << *MI); ----
1019 NonPredicated.insert(MI); 0
1020 break; 0
1021 } ----
1022 } ----
1023 // Any unknown false lanes have been masked away by the user(s). ----
1024 if (!NonPredicated.contains(MI)) 0
1025 Predicated.insert(MI); 0
1026 } ----
1027 ----
1028 SmallPtrSet LiveOutMIs; 0
1029 SmallVector ExitBlocks; 0
1030 ML.getExitBlocks(ExitBlocks); 0
1031 assert(ML.getNumBlocks() == 1 && "Expected single block loop!"); 0
1032 assert(ExitBlocks.size() == 1 && "Expected a single exit block"); 0
1033 MachineBasicBlock *ExitBB = ExitBlocks.front(); 0
1034 for (const MachineBasicBlock::RegisterMaskPair &RegMask : ExitBB->liveins()) { 0
1035 // TODO: Instead of blocking predication, we could move the vctp to the exit ----
1036 // block and calculate it's operand there in or the preheader. ----
1037 if (RegMask.PhysReg == ARM::VPR) { 0
1038 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " VPR is live in to the exit block."); 0
1039 return false; 0
1040 } ----
1041 // Check Q-regs that are live in the exit blocks. We don't collect scalars ----
1042 // because they won't be affected by lane predication. ----
1043 if (QPRs->contains(RegMask.PhysReg)) 0
1044 if (auto *MI = RDA.getLocalLiveOutMIDef(Header, RegMask.PhysReg)) 0
1045 LiveOutMIs.insert(MI); 0
1046 } ----
1047 ----
1048 // We've already validated that any VPT predication within the loop will be ----
1049 // equivalent when we perform the predication transformation; so we know that ----
1050 // any VPT predicated instruction is predicated upon VCTP. Any live-out ----
1051 // instruction needs to be predicated, so check this here. The instructions ----
1052 // in NonPredicated have been found to be a reduction that we can ensure its ----
1053 // legality. Any MQPRCopy found will need to validate its input as if it was ----
1054 // live out. ----
1055 SmallVector Worklist(LiveOutMIs.begin(), LiveOutMIs.end()); 0
1056 while (!Worklist.empty()) { 0
1057 MachineInstr *MI = Worklist.pop_back_val(); 0
1058 if (MI->getOpcode() == ARM::MQPRCopy) { 0
1059 VMOVCopies.insert(MI); 0
1060 MachineInstr *CopySrc = ----
1061 RDA.getUniqueReachingMIDef(MI, MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1062 if (CopySrc) 0
1063 Worklist.push_back(CopySrc); 0
1064 } else if (NonPredicated.count(MI) && FalseLanesUnknown.contains(MI)) { 0
1065 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Unable to handle live out: " << *MI); 0
1066 VMOVCopies.clear(); 0
1067 return false; 0
1068 } ----
1069 } ----
1070 ----
1071 return true; 0
1072 } 0
1073 ----
1074 void LowOverheadLoop::Validate(ARMBasicBlockUtils *BBUtils) { 0
1075 if (Revert) 0
1076 return; 0
1077 ----
1078 // Check branch target ranges: WLS[TP] can only branch forwards and LE[TP] ----
1079 // can only jump back. ----
1080 auto ValidateRanges = [](MachineInstr *Start, MachineInstr *End, 0
1081 ARMBasicBlockUtils *BBUtils, MachineLoop &ML) { ----
1082 MachineBasicBlock *TgtBB = End->getOpcode() == ARM::t2LoopEnd 0
1083 ? End->getOperand(1).getMBB() 0
1084 : End->getOperand(2).getMBB(); 0
1085 // TODO Maybe there's cases where the target doesn't have to be the header, ----
1086 // but for now be safe and revert. ----
1087 if (TgtBB != ML.getHeader()) { 0
1088 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: LoopEnd is not targeting header.\n"); 0
1089 return false; 0
1090 } ----
1091 ----
1092 // The WLS and LE instructions have 12-bits for the label offset. WLS ----
1093 // requires a positive offset, while LE uses negative. ----
1094 if (BBUtils->getOffsetOf(End) < BBUtils->getOffsetOf(ML.getHeader()) || 0
1095 !BBUtils->isBBInRange(End, ML.getHeader(), 4094)) { 0
1096 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: LE offset is out-of-range\n"); 0
1097 return false; 0
1098 } ----
1099 ----
1100 if (isWhileLoopStart(*Start)) { 0
1101 MachineBasicBlock *TargetBB = getWhileLoopStartTargetBB(*Start); 0
1102 if (BBUtils->getOffsetOf(Start) > BBUtils->getOffsetOf(TargetBB) || 0
1103 !BBUtils->isBBInRange(Start, TargetBB, 4094)) { 0
1104 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: WLS offset is out-of-range!\n"); 0
1105 return false; 0
1106 } ----
1107 } ----
1108 return true; 0
1109 }; ----
1110 ----
1111 StartInsertPt = MachineBasicBlock::iterator(Start); 0
1112 StartInsertBB = Start->getParent(); 0
1113 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Will insert LoopStart at " 0
1114 << *StartInsertPt); ----
1115 ----
1116 Revert = !ValidateRanges(Start, End, BBUtils, ML); 0
1117 CannotTailPredicate = !ValidateTailPredicate(); 0
1118 } ----
1119 ----
1120 bool LowOverheadLoop::AddVCTP(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1121 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Adding VCTP: " << *MI); 0
1122 if (VCTPs.empty()) { 0
1123 VCTPs.push_back(MI); 0
1124 return true; 0
1125 } ----
1126 ----
1127 // If we find another VCTP, check whether it uses the same value as the main VCTP. ----
1128 // If it does, store it in the VCTPs set, else refuse it. ----
1129 MachineInstr *Prev = VCTPs.back(); 0
1130 if (!Prev->getOperand(1).isIdenticalTo(MI->getOperand(1)) || 0
1131 !RDA.hasSameReachingDef(Prev, MI, MI->getOperand(1).getReg().asMCReg())) { 0
1132 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Found VCTP with a different reaching " 0
1133 "definition from the main VCTP"); ----
1134 return false; 0
1135 } ----
1136 VCTPs.push_back(MI); 0
1137 return true; 0
1138 } ----
1139 ----
1140 static bool ValidateMVEStore(MachineInstr *MI, MachineLoop *ML) { 0
1141 ----
1142 auto GetFrameIndex = [](MachineMemOperand *Operand) { 0
1143 const PseudoSourceValue *PseudoValue = Operand->getPseudoValue(); 0
1144 if (PseudoValue && PseudoValue->kind() == PseudoSourceValue::FixedStack) { 0
1145 if (const auto *FS = dyn_cast(PseudoValue)) { 0
1146 return FS->getFrameIndex(); 0
1147 } ----
1148 } ----
1149 return -1; 0
1150 }; ----
1151 ----
1152 auto IsStackOp = [GetFrameIndex](MachineInstr *I) { 0
1153 switch (I->getOpcode()) { 0
1154 case ARM::MVE_VSTRWU32: 0
1155 case ARM::MVE_VLDRWU32: { ----
1156 return I->getOperand(1).getReg() == ARM::SP && 0
1157 I->memoperands().size() == 1 && 0
1158 GetFrameIndex(I->memoperands().front()) >= 0; 0
1159 } ----
1160 default: 0
1161 return false; 0
1162 } ----
1163 }; ----
1164 ----
1165 // An unpredicated vector register spill is allowed if all of the uses of the ----
1166 // stack slot are within the loop ----
1167 if (MI->getOpcode() != ARM::MVE_VSTRWU32 || !IsStackOp(MI)) 0
1168 return false; 0
1169 ----
1170 // Search all blocks after the loop for accesses to the same stack slot. ----
1171 // ReachingDefAnalysis doesn't work for sp as it relies on registers being ----
1172 // live-out (which sp never is) to know what blocks to look in ----
1173 if (MI->memoperands().size() == 0) 0
1174 return false; 0
1175 int FI = GetFrameIndex(MI->memoperands().front()); 0
1176 ----
1177 auto &FrameInfo = MI->getParent()->getParent()->getFrameInfo(); 0
1178 if (FI == -1 || !FrameInfo.isSpillSlotObjectIndex(FI)) 0
1179 return false; 0
1180 ----
1181 SmallVector Frontier; 0
1182 ML->getExitBlocks(Frontier); 0
1183 SmallPtrSet Visited{MI->getParent()}; 0
1184 unsigned Idx = 0; 0
1185 while (Idx < Frontier.size()) { 0
1186 MachineBasicBlock *BB = Frontier[Idx]; 0
1187 bool LookAtSuccessors = true; 0
1188 for (auto &I : *BB) { 0
1189 if (!IsStackOp(&I) || I.memoperands().size() == 0) 0
1190 continue; 0
1191 if (GetFrameIndex(I.memoperands().front()) != FI) 0
1192 continue; 0
1193 // If this block has a store to the stack slot before any loads then we ----
1194 // can ignore the block ----
1195 if (I.getOpcode() == ARM::MVE_VSTRWU32) { 0
1196 LookAtSuccessors = false; 0
1197 break; 0
1198 } ----
1199 // If the store and the load are using the same stack slot then the ----
1200 // store isn't valid for tail predication ----
1201 if (I.getOpcode() == ARM::MVE_VLDRWU32) 0
1202 return false; 0
1203 } ----
1204 ----
1205 if (LookAtSuccessors) { 0
1206 for (auto *Succ : BB->successors()) { 0
1207 if (!Visited.contains(Succ) && !is_contained(Frontier, Succ)) 0
1208 Frontier.push_back(Succ); 0
1209 } ----
1210 } ----
1211 Visited.insert(BB); 0
1212 Idx++; 0
1213 } ----
1214 ----
1215 return true; 0
1216 } 0
1217 ----
1218 bool LowOverheadLoop::ValidateMVEInst(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1219 if (CannotTailPredicate) 0
1220 return false; 0
1221 ----
1222 if (!shouldInspect(*MI)) 0
1223 return true; 0
1224 ----
1225 if (MI->getOpcode() == ARM::MVE_VPSEL || 0
1226 MI->getOpcode() == ARM::MVE_VPNOT) { 0
1227 // TODO: Allow VPSEL and VPNOT, we currently cannot because: ----
1228 // 1) It will use the VPR as a predicate operand, but doesn't have to be ----
1229 // instead a VPT block, which means we can assert while building up ----
1230 // the VPT block because we don't find another VPT or VPST to being a new ----
1231 // one. ----
1232 // 2) VPSEL still requires a VPR operand even after tail predicating, ----
1233 // which means we can't remove it unless there is another ----
1234 // instruction, such as vcmp, that can provide the VPR def. ----
1235 return false; 0
1236 } ----
1237 ----
1238 // Record all VCTPs and check that they're equivalent to one another. ----
1239 if (isVCTP(MI) && !AddVCTP(MI)) 0
1240 return false; 0
1241 ----
1242 // Inspect uses first so that any instructions that alter the VPR don't ----
1243 // alter the predicate upon themselves. ----
1244 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MI->getDesc(); 0
1245 bool IsUse = false; 0
1246 unsigned LastOpIdx = MI->getNumOperands() - 1; 0
1247 for (const auto &Op : enumerate(reverse(MCID.operands()))) { 0
1248 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(LastOpIdx - Op.index()); 0
1249 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isUse() || MO.getReg() != ARM::VPR) 0
1250 continue; 0
1251 ----
1252 if (ARM::isVpred(Op.value().OperandType)) { 0
1253 VPTState::addInst(MI); 0
1254 IsUse = true; 0
1255 } else if (MI->getOpcode() != ARM::MVE_VPST) { 0
1256 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Found instruction using vpr: " << *MI); 0
1257 return false; 0
1258 } ----
1259 } ----
1260 ----
1261 // If we find an instruction that has been marked as not valid for tail ----
1262 // predication, only allow the instruction if it's contained within a valid ----
1263 // VPT block. ----
1264 bool RequiresExplicitPredication = 0
1265 (MCID.TSFlags & ARMII::ValidForTailPredication) == 0; 0
1266 if (isDomainMVE(MI) && RequiresExplicitPredication) { 0
1267 if (MI->getOpcode() == ARM::MQPRCopy) 0
1268 return true; 0
1269 if (!IsUse && producesDoubleWidthResult(*MI)) { 0
1270 DoubleWidthResultInstrs.insert(MI); 0
1271 return true; 0
1272 } ----
1273 ----
1274 LLVM_DEBUG(if (!IsUse) dbgs() 0
1275 << "ARM Loops: Can't tail predicate: " << *MI); ----
1276 return IsUse; 0
1277 } ----
1278 ----
1279 // If the instruction is already explicitly predicated, then the conversion ----
1280 // will be fine, but ensure that all store operations are predicated. ----
1281 if (MI->mayStore() && !ValidateMVEStore(MI, &ML)) 0
1282 return IsUse; 0
1283 ----
1284 // If this instruction defines the VPR, update the predicate for the ----
1285 // proceeding instructions. ----
1286 if (isVectorPredicate(MI)) { 0
1287 // Clear the existing predicate when we're not in VPT Active state, ----
1288 // otherwise we add to it. ----
1289 if (!isVectorPredicated(MI)) 0
1290 VPTState::resetPredicate(MI); 0
1291 else ----
1292 VPTState::addPredicate(MI); 0
1293 } ----
1294 ----
1295 // Finally once the predicate has been modified, we can start a new VPT ----
1296 // block if necessary. ----
1297 if (isVPTOpcode(MI->getOpcode())) 0
1298 VPTState::CreateVPTBlock(MI); 0
1299 ----
1300 return true; 0
1301 } ----
1302 ----
1303 bool ARMLowOverheadLoops::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &mf) { 0
1304 const ARMSubtarget &ST = mf.getSubtarget(); 0
1305 if (!ST.hasLOB()) 0
1306 return false; 0
1307 ----
1308 MF = &mf; 0
1309 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops on " << MF->getName() << " ------------- \n"); 0
1310 ----
1311 MLI = &getAnalysis(); 0
1312 RDA = &getAnalysis(); 0
1313 MF->getProperties().set(MachineFunctionProperties::Property::TracksLiveness); 0
1314 MRI = &MF->getRegInfo(); 0
1315 TII = static_cast(ST.getInstrInfo()); 0
1316 TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
1317 BBUtils = std::unique_ptr(new ARMBasicBlockUtils(*MF)); 0
1318 BBUtils->computeAllBlockSizes(); 0
1319 BBUtils->adjustBBOffsetsAfter(&MF->front()); 0
1320 ----
1321 bool Changed = false; 0
1322 for (auto *ML : *MLI) { 0
1323 if (ML->isOutermost()) 0
1324 Changed |= ProcessLoop(ML); 0
1325 } ----
1326 Changed |= RevertNonLoops(); 0
1327 return Changed; 0
1328 } ----
1329 ----
1330 bool ARMLowOverheadLoops::ProcessLoop(MachineLoop *ML) { 0
1331 ----
1332 bool Changed = false; 0
1333 ----
1334 // Process inner loops first. ----
1335 for (MachineLoop *L : *ML) 0
1336 Changed |= ProcessLoop(L); 0
1337 ----
1338 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
1339 dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Processing loop containing:\n"; ----
1340 if (auto *Preheader = ML->getLoopPreheader()) ----
1341 dbgs() << " - Preheader: " << printMBBReference(*Preheader) << "\n"; ----
1342 else if (auto *Preheader = MLI->findLoopPreheader(ML, true, true)) ----
1343 dbgs() << " - Preheader: " << printMBBReference(*Preheader) << "\n"; ----
1344 for (auto *MBB : ML->getBlocks()) ----
1345 dbgs() << " - Block: " << printMBBReference(*MBB) << "\n"; ----
1346 }); ----
1347 ----
1348 // Search the given block for a loop start instruction. If one isn't found, ----
1349 // and there's only one predecessor block, search that one too. ----
1350 std::function SearchForStart = ----
1351 [&SearchForStart](MachineBasicBlock *MBB) -> MachineInstr* { 0
1352 for (auto &MI : *MBB) { 0
1353 if (isLoopStart(MI)) 0
1354 return &MI; 0
1355 } ----
1356 if (MBB->pred_size() == 1) 0
1357 return SearchForStart(*MBB->pred_begin()); 0
1358 return nullptr; 0
1359 }; 0
1360 ----
1361 LowOverheadLoop LoLoop(*ML, *MLI, *RDA, *TRI, *TII); 0
1362 // Search the preheader for the start intrinsic. ----
1363 // FIXME: I don't see why we shouldn't be supporting multiple predecessors ----
1364 // with potentially multiple set.loop.iterations, so we need to enable this. ----
1365 if (LoLoop.Preheader) 0
1366 LoLoop.Start = SearchForStart(LoLoop.Preheader); 0
1367 else ----
1368 return Changed; 0
1369 ----
1370 // Find the low-overhead loop components and decide whether or not to fall ----
1371 // back to a normal loop. Also look for a vctp instructions and decide ----
1372 // whether we can convert that predicate using tail predication. ----
1373 for (auto *MBB : reverse(ML->getBlocks())) { 0
1374 for (auto &MI : *MBB) { 0
1375 if (MI.isDebugValue()) 0
1376 continue; 0
1377 else if (MI.getOpcode() == ARM::t2LoopDec) 0
1378 LoLoop.Dec = &MI; 0
1379 else if (MI.getOpcode() == ARM::t2LoopEnd) 0
1380 LoLoop.End = &MI; 0
1381 else if (MI.getOpcode() == ARM::t2LoopEndDec) 0
1382 LoLoop.End = LoLoop.Dec = &MI; 0
1383 else if (isLoopStart(MI)) 0
1384 LoLoop.Start = &MI; 0
1385 else if (MI.getDesc().isCall()) { 0
1386 // TODO: Though the call will require LE to execute again, does this ----
1387 // mean we should revert? Always executing LE hopefully should be ----
1388 // faster than performing a sub,cmp,br or even subs,br. ----
1389 LoLoop.Revert = true; 0
1390 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Found call.\n"); 0
1391 } else { ----
1392 // Record VPR defs and build up their corresponding vpt blocks. ----
1393 // Check we know how to tail predicate any mve instructions. ----
1394 LoLoop.AnalyseMVEInst(&MI); 0
1395 } ----
1396 } ----
1397 } ----
1398 ----
1399 LLVM_DEBUG(LoLoop.dump()); 0
1400 if (!LoLoop.FoundAllComponents()) { 0
1401 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Didn't find loop start, update, end\n"); 0
1402 return Changed; 0
1403 } ----
1404 ----
1405 assert(LoLoop.Start->getOpcode() != ARM::t2WhileLoopStart && 0
1406 "Expected t2WhileLoopStart to be removed before regalloc!"); ----
1407 ----
1408 // Check that the only instruction using LoopDec is LoopEnd. This can only ----
1409 // happen when the Dec and End are separate, not a single t2LoopEndDec. ----
1410 // TODO: Check for copy chains that really have no effect. ----
1411 if (LoLoop.Dec != LoLoop.End) { 0
1412 SmallPtrSet Uses; 0
1413 RDA->getReachingLocalUses(LoLoop.Dec, MCRegister::from(ARM::LR), Uses); 0
1414 if (Uses.size() > 1 || !Uses.count(LoLoop.End)) { 0
1415 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Unable to remove LoopDec.\n"); 0
1416 LoLoop.Revert = true; 0
1417 } ----
1418 } 0
1419 LoLoop.Validate(BBUtils.get()); 0
1420 Expand(LoLoop); 0
1421 return true; 0
1422 } 0
1423 ----
1424 // WhileLoopStart holds the exit block, so produce a cmp lr, 0 and then a ----
1425 // beq that branches to the exit branch. ----
1426 // TODO: We could also try to generate a cbz if the value in LR is also in ----
1427 // another low register. ----
1428 void ARMLowOverheadLoops::RevertWhile(MachineInstr *MI) const { 0
1429 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Reverting to cmp: " << *MI); 0
1430 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB = getWhileLoopStartTargetBB(*MI); 0
1431 unsigned BrOpc = BBUtils->isBBInRange(MI, DestBB, 254) ? 0
1432 ARM::tBcc : ARM::t2Bcc; 0
1433 ----
1434 RevertWhileLoopStartLR(MI, TII, BrOpc); 0
1435 } 0
1436 ----
1437 void ARMLowOverheadLoops::RevertDo(MachineInstr *MI) const { 0
1438 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Reverting to mov: " << *MI); 0
1439 RevertDoLoopStart(MI, TII); 0
1440 } 0
1441 ----
1442 bool ARMLowOverheadLoops::RevertLoopDec(MachineInstr *MI) const { 0
1443 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Reverting to sub: " << *MI); 0
1444 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent(); 0
1445 SmallPtrSet Ignore; 0
1446 for (auto I = MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI), E = MBB->end(); I != E; ++I) { 0
1447 if (I->getOpcode() == ARM::t2LoopEnd) { 0
1448 Ignore.insert(&*I); 0
1449 break; 0
1450 } ----
1451 } ----
1452 ----
1453 // If nothing defines CPSR between LoopDec and LoopEnd, use a t2SUBS. ----
1454 bool SetFlags = ----
1455 RDA->isSafeToDefRegAt(MI, MCRegister::from(ARM::CPSR), Ignore); 0
1456 ----
1457 llvm::RevertLoopDec(MI, TII, SetFlags); 0
1458 return SetFlags; 0
1459 } 0
1460 ----
1461 // Generate a subs, or sub and cmp, and a branch instead of an LE. ----
1462 void ARMLowOverheadLoops::RevertLoopEnd(MachineInstr *MI, bool SkipCmp) const { 0
1463 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Reverting to cmp, br: " << *MI); 0
1464 ----
1465 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB = MI->getOperand(1).getMBB(); 0
1466 unsigned BrOpc = BBUtils->isBBInRange(MI, DestBB, 254) ? 0
1467 ARM::tBcc : ARM::t2Bcc; 0
1468 ----
1469 llvm::RevertLoopEnd(MI, TII, BrOpc, SkipCmp); 0
1470 } 0
1471 ----
1472 // Generate a subs, or sub and cmp, and a branch instead of an LE. ----
1473 void ARMLowOverheadLoops::RevertLoopEndDec(MachineInstr *MI) const { 0
1474 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Reverting to subs, br: " << *MI); 0
1475 assert(MI->getOpcode() == ARM::t2LoopEndDec && "Expected a t2LoopEndDec!"); 0
1476 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent(); 0
1477 ----
1478 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
1479 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::t2SUBri)); 0
1480 MIB.addDef(ARM::LR); 0
1481 MIB.add(MI->getOperand(1)); 0
1482 MIB.addImm(1); 0
1483 MIB.addImm(ARMCC::AL); 0
1484 MIB.addReg(ARM::NoRegister); 0
1485 MIB.addReg(ARM::CPSR); 0
1486 MIB->getOperand(5).setIsDef(true); 0
1487 ----
1488 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB = MI->getOperand(2).getMBB(); 0
1489 unsigned BrOpc = ----
1490 BBUtils->isBBInRange(MI, DestBB, 254) ? ARM::tBcc : ARM::t2Bcc; 0
1491 ----
1492 // Create bne ----
1493 MIB = BuildMI(*MBB, MI, MI->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(BrOpc)); 0
1494 MIB.add(MI->getOperand(2)); // branch target 0
1495 MIB.addImm(ARMCC::NE); // condition code 0
1496 MIB.addReg(ARM::CPSR); 0
1497 ----
1498 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1499 } 0
1500 ----
1501 // Perform dead code elimation on the loop iteration count setup expression. ----
1502 // If we are tail-predicating, the number of elements to be processed is the ----
1503 // operand of the VCTP instruction in the vector body, see getCount(), which is ----
1504 // register $r3 in this example: ----
1505 // ----
1506 // $lr = big-itercount-expression ----
1507 // .. ----
1508 // $lr = t2DoLoopStart renamable $lr ----
1509 // vector.body: ----
1510 // .. ----
1511 // $vpr = MVE_VCTP32 renamable $r3 ----
1512 // renamable $lr = t2LoopDec killed renamable $lr, 1 ----
1513 // t2LoopEnd renamable $lr, %vector.body ----
1514 // tB %end ----
1515 // ----
1516 // What we would like achieve here is to replace the do-loop start pseudo ----
1517 // instruction t2DoLoopStart with: ----
1518 // ----
1519 // $lr = MVE_DLSTP_32 killed renamable $r3 ----
1520 // ----
1521 // Thus, $r3 which defines the number of elements, is written to $lr, ----
1522 // and then we want to delete the whole chain that used to define $lr, ----
1523 // see the comment below how this chain could look like. ----
1524 // ----
1525 void ARMLowOverheadLoops::IterationCountDCE(LowOverheadLoop &LoLoop) { 0
1526 if (!LoLoop.IsTailPredicationLegal()) 0
1527 return; 0
1528 ----
1529 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Trying DCE on loop iteration count.\n"); 0
1530 ----
1531 MachineInstr *Def = RDA->getMIOperand(LoLoop.Start, 1); 0
1532 if (!Def) { 0
1533 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Couldn't find iteration count.\n"); 0
1534 return; 0
1535 } ----
1536 ----
1537 // Collect and remove the users of iteration count. ----
1538 SmallPtrSet Killed = { LoLoop.Start, LoLoop.Dec, 0
1539 LoLoop.End }; 0
1540 if (!TryRemove(Def, *RDA, LoLoop.ToRemove, Killed)) 0
1541 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Unsafe to remove loop iteration count.\n"); 0
1542 } 0
1543 ----
1544 MachineInstr* ARMLowOverheadLoops::ExpandLoopStart(LowOverheadLoop &LoLoop) { 0
1545 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Expanding LoopStart.\n"); 0
1546 // When using tail-predication, try to delete the dead code that was used to ----
1547 // calculate the number of loop iterations. ----
1548 IterationCountDCE(LoLoop); 0
1549 ----
1550 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertPt = LoLoop.StartInsertPt; 0
1551 MachineInstr *Start = LoLoop.Start; 0
1552 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = LoLoop.StartInsertBB; 0
1553 unsigned Opc = LoLoop.getStartOpcode(); 0
1554 MachineOperand &Count = LoLoop.getLoopStartOperand(); 0
1555 ----
1556 // A DLS lr, lr we needn't emit ----
1557 MachineInstr* NewStart; ----
1558 if (!DisableOmitDLS && Opc == ARM::t2DLS && Count.isReg() && 0
1559 Count.getReg() == ARM::LR) { 0
1560 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Didn't insert start: DLS lr, lr"); 0
1561 NewStart = nullptr; 0
1562 } else { ----
1563 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
1564 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertPt, Start->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(Opc)); 0
1565 ----
1566 MIB.addDef(ARM::LR); 0
1567 MIB.add(Count); 0
1568 if (isWhileLoopStart(*Start)) 0
1569 MIB.addMBB(getWhileLoopStartTargetBB(*Start)); 0
1570 ----
1571 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Inserted start: " << *MIB); 0
1572 NewStart = &*MIB; 0
1573 } ----
1574 ----
1575 LoLoop.ToRemove.insert(Start); 0
1576 return NewStart; 0
1577 } ----
1578 ----
1579 void ARMLowOverheadLoops::ConvertVPTBlocks(LowOverheadLoop &LoLoop) { 0
1580 auto RemovePredicate = [](MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1581 if (MI->isDebugInstr()) 0
1582 return; 0
1583 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Removing predicate from: " << *MI); 0
1584 int PIdx = llvm::findFirstVPTPredOperandIdx(*MI); 0
1585 assert(PIdx >= 1 && "Trying to unpredicate a non-predicated instruction"); 0
1586 assert(MI->getOperand(PIdx).getImm() == ARMVCC::Then && 0
1587 "Expected Then predicate!"); ----
1588 MI->getOperand(PIdx).setImm(ARMVCC::None); 0
1589 MI->getOperand(PIdx + 1).setReg(0); 0
1590 }; ----
1591 ----
1592 for (auto &Block : LoLoop.getVPTBlocks()) { 0
1593 SmallVectorImpl &Insts = Block.getInsts(); 0
1594 ----
1595 auto ReplaceVCMPWithVPT = [&](MachineInstr *&TheVCMP, MachineInstr *At) { 0
1596 assert(TheVCMP && "Replacing a removed or non-existent VCMP"); 0
1597 // Replace the VCMP with a VPT ----
1598 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
1599 BuildMI(*At->getParent(), At, At->getDebugLoc(), 0
1600 TII->get(VCMPOpcodeToVPT(TheVCMP->getOpcode()))); 0
1601 MIB.addImm(ARMVCC::Then); 0
1602 // Register one ----
1603 MIB.add(TheVCMP->getOperand(1)); 0
1604 // Register two ----
1605 MIB.add(TheVCMP->getOperand(2)); 0
1606 // The comparison code, e.g. ge, eq, lt ----
1607 MIB.add(TheVCMP->getOperand(3)); 0
1608 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Combining with VCMP to VPT: " << *MIB); 0
1609 LoLoop.BlockMasksToRecompute.insert(MIB.getInstr()); 0
1610 LoLoop.ToRemove.insert(TheVCMP); 0
1611 TheVCMP = nullptr; 0
1612 }; 0
1613 ----
1614 if (VPTState::isEntryPredicatedOnVCTP(Block, /*exclusive*/ true)) { 0
1615 MachineInstr *VPST = Insts.front(); 0
1616 if (VPTState::hasUniformPredicate(Block)) { 0
1617 // A vpt block starting with VPST, is only predicated upon vctp and has no ----
1618 // internal vpr defs: ----
1619 // - Remove vpst. ----
1620 // - Unpredicate the remaining instructions. ----
1621 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Removing VPST: " << *VPST); 0
1622 for (unsigned i = 1; i < Insts.size(); ++i) 0
1623 RemovePredicate(Insts[i]); 0
1624 } else { ----
1625 // The VPT block has a non-uniform predicate but it uses a vpst and its ----
1626 // entry is guarded only by a vctp, which means we: ----
1627 // - Need to remove the original vpst. ----
1628 // - Then need to unpredicate any following instructions, until ----
1629 // we come across the divergent vpr def. ----
1630 // - Insert a new vpst to predicate the instruction(s) that following ----
1631 // the divergent vpr def. ----
1632 MachineInstr *Divergent = VPTState::getDivergent(Block); 0
1633 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = Divergent->getParent(); 0
1634 auto DivergentNext = ++MachineBasicBlock::iterator(Divergent); 0
1635 while (DivergentNext != MBB->end() && DivergentNext->isDebugInstr()) 0
1636 ++DivergentNext; 0
1637 ----
1638 bool DivergentNextIsPredicated = ----
1639 DivergentNext != MBB->end() && 0
1640 getVPTInstrPredicate(*DivergentNext) != ARMVCC::None; 0
1641 ----
1642 for (auto I = ++MachineBasicBlock::iterator(VPST), E = DivergentNext; 0
1643 I != E; ++I) 0
1644 RemovePredicate(&*I); 0
1645 ----
1646 // Check if the instruction defining vpr is a vcmp so it can be combined ----
1647 // with the VPST This should be the divergent instruction ----
1648 MachineInstr *VCMP = ----
1649 VCMPOpcodeToVPT(Divergent->getOpcode()) != 0 ? Divergent : nullptr; 0
1650 ----
1651 if (DivergentNextIsPredicated) { 0
1652 // Insert a VPST at the divergent only if the next instruction ----
1653 // would actually use it. A VCMP following a VPST can be ----
1654 // merged into a VPT so do that instead if the VCMP exists. ----
1655 if (!VCMP) { 0
1656 // Create a VPST (with a null mask for now, we'll recompute it ----
1657 // later) ----
1658 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = ----
1659 BuildMI(*Divergent->getParent(), Divergent, 0
1660 Divergent->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::MVE_VPST)); 0
1661 MIB.addImm(0); 0
1662 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Created VPST: " << *MIB); 0
1663 LoLoop.BlockMasksToRecompute.insert(MIB.getInstr()); 0
1664 } else { ----
1665 // No RDA checks are necessary here since the VPST would have been ----
1666 // directly after the VCMP ----
1667 ReplaceVCMPWithVPT(VCMP, VCMP); 0
1668 } ----
1669 } ----
1670 } ----
1671 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ARM Loops: Removing VPST: " << *VPST); 0
1672 LoLoop.ToRemove.insert(VPST); 0
1673 } else if (Block.containsVCTP()) { 0
1674 // The vctp will be removed, so either the entire block will be dead or ----
1675 // the block mask of the vp(s)t will need to be recomputed. ----
1676 MachineInstr *VPST = Insts.front(); 0
1677 if (Block.size() == 2) { 0
1678 assert(VPST->getOpcode() == ARM::MVE_VPST && 0
1679 "Found a VPST in an otherwise empty vpt block"); ----
1680 LoLoop.ToRemove.insert(VPST); 0
1681 } else ----
1682 LoLoop.BlockMasksToRecompute.insert(VPST); 0
1683 } else if (Insts.front()->getOpcode() == ARM::MVE_VPST) { 0
1684 // If this block starts with a VPST then attempt to merge it with the ----
1685 // preceeding un-merged VCMP into a VPT. This VCMP comes from a VPT ----
1686 // block that no longer exists ----
1687 MachineInstr *VPST = Insts.front(); 0
1688 auto Next = ++MachineBasicBlock::iterator(VPST); 0
1689 assert(getVPTInstrPredicate(*Next) != ARMVCC::None && 0
1690 "The instruction after a VPST must be predicated"); ----
1691 (void)Next; ----
1692 MachineInstr *VprDef = RDA->getUniqueReachingMIDef(VPST, ARM::VPR); 0
1693 if (VprDef && VCMPOpcodeToVPT(VprDef->getOpcode()) && 0
1694 !LoLoop.ToRemove.contains(VprDef)) { 0
1695 MachineInstr *VCMP = VprDef; 0
1696 // The VCMP and VPST can only be merged if the VCMP's operands will have ----
1697 // the same values at the VPST. ----
1698 // If any of the instructions between the VCMP and VPST are predicated ----
1699 // then a different code path is expected to have merged the VCMP and ----
1700 // VPST already. ----
1701 if (std::none_of(++MachineBasicBlock::iterator(VCMP), 0
1702 MachineBasicBlock::iterator(VPST), hasVPRUse) && 0
1703 RDA->hasSameReachingDef(VCMP, VPST, VCMP->getOperand(1).getReg()) && 0
1704 RDA->hasSameReachingDef(VCMP, VPST, VCMP->getOperand(2).getReg())) { 0
